<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-04-25T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-04-25T12:00:00-05:00" n="546" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d546">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/1172: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-25T12:00:00-05:00">April 25,
                                1929—noon</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>137. Your 295, April 19, 6 p.m. Please telegraph what if any are the
                            present Chinese Government restrictions on importation of arms.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>